name: PixelFem #64 - Nancy Wake
description:
Nancy was an Australian woman from humble beginnings in Sydney who became the most decorated woman of World War II. During this time Nancy had a five-million-franc price put on her head by the feared German secret police, the Gestapo, for helping the French Resistance. Branded the White Mouse, for her uncanny ability to run rings around the Gestapo, she became the most wanted resistance fighter in France.

✺This work is part of PixelFems, an evolving project on the Tezos blockchain celebrating iconic women from the past and present✺
